item.title: Willow + Banker
item.dc:creator: @Rune_Hacker1 Rune Hacker
item.description:
@Rune_Hacker1 wrote:

Im sorry, but thats a horrible script.

You need failsafes, more reliable functions, not using clickmouse (which you use wrong anyways), and your main loop is way wrong and doesnt work right. You need antirandoms, anti-ban, and a bunch of other stuff.

Your banking procedure it bad also. There is a built in bank opener, its called openbankglass; or soemthing like that. Its in the srl manual. You should put a lot of work into evey scrit you make. Don’t rush the release, wait till it all works. You can get a lot of help here: http://www.srl-forums.com/forum/ many tutorials, and scripts to look through.

MANY of your functions arent right like you have Mouse(x,y) when it should be Mouse(x,y,1,1,True). Please just dont ruch a release, take your time on all of your scripts and make sure they work good.

item.title: Willow + Banker
item.dc:creator: @seaking seaking
item.description:
@seaking wrote:

Woa Woa stop what is this?

Mouse(x,y); Wait(4000)+random(3000); ClickMouse(x,y,left,true); <<<<<<<<<--------- Wait(3000); MakeCompass('N');
First of all it’s clickmouse. Second it’s not even coded correctly.
NEVER use clickmouse, just use Mouse instead. And about the parameters… why do you have left,true in there? Clickmouse is like this…: ClickMouse(x,y,left);
You replace left with true.

About the script, it doesn’t compile. Are you sure you posted the right one?

thanks i will test this out, and post any bugs later

Sorry for the flame… ish… but you have a lot to learn
